description._content: ID: 059640 Title: A Collection of Drawings made in the Countries visited by Captain Cook in his First Voyage Illustrator: "Parkinson, Sydney (Sydney Parkinson)" Provenance: [1] 1769; [2] 1773 Caption: Portrait of a New Zealand man Notes: [Whole folio] Portrait of Otegoowgoow [Otegoonoon], son of a chief of the Bay of Islands. He has a comb in his hair, an ornament of green stone in his ear, and another of a fish's tooth round his neck. Joseph Banks records meeting him on 3 December 1769. Drawing by Sydney Parkinson, circa December 1769, with engraving below Image taken from A Collection of Drawings made in the Countries visited by Captain Cook in his First Voyage. 1768-1771. Originally published/produced in [1] 1769; [2] 1773.
